        <tr>
          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody"><span style="font-style: italic"><span style="color: yellow">Sassee: A ton of solo content has been added to the game recently, anyone who keeps track of patch notes (like myself) can attest to that. Can you elaborate on more plans towards solo and small group content in more detail? Currently, a lot of players are still asking what’s next.
<br />
  
<br />
Steve "Moorgard" Danuser: Live Update #4, currently on Test and moving to the live servers next week, includes big changes for soloers and small-group players. Experience has again been increased (especially over level 30), and new types of treasure are available. Many players on Test have reported being extremely satisfied that they can now <span style="font-weight: bold">accumulate worthwhile loot and spell upgrades without requiring a full group to obtain them</span>. We're also in the continuing process of adding solo quest paths that guide you through all levels so that solo and small-group players feel they have direction and goals. Plus, there is a new solo adventure area available called the Valley of the Rogue Magi, located in Commonlands. Expect to see more such instances in the future.</span></span>
<br />

<br />
EQ2 is doing a great job.  I am amazed at the amount of new stuff they introduce continuously to the game.  My biggest concern (and most self directed) is the separation of Casual and Hardcore loot.  
<br />

<br />
At the top end of the game the "Metal Chest" seems to share the same loot table.  Which means a Casual game can score anything a hardcore gamer can off of a random metal chest drop from exp mobs that con blue.  <span style="font-weight: bold">This is my issue</span>.  I spend gross amounts of time on this game.  Most of my guildies do as well.  We kill / raid everymob everyday.  Why?  Loots of course...  Next moment I inspect a person in a non raiding guild and see they have just about the same armor and accessories as me, but no where near as much time invested or effort.   NOW - Live update will make solo loot even better and easier to get... great, nice work.  Way to make a TEAM of people feel like they are being productive everynight raiding for 6 hours and getting the same quality shit as a solo play...  HELLO?  McFly?  Anybody home?
<br />

<br />
Kill Epic mob x4 lvl 55 - Get AWESOME ring.   Kill Flower x2 in Feerrott - get same ring.  What?  How did pewnie flower mob score the same uber ring that Huge fucking giant with an Axe has?  Can someone explain the rational behind this to me.  Is this just a lack of some person wanting to code each mob with some loot table?   What I am seeing is you can be at 45+... kill x2 mobs and normal grouped named mobs and get a crap load of rares and the same loot as x4 mobs.  Sorry, I want challenge... for my guild and myself.... and I want rewards... Uber fucking rewards... for myself and the guild that defeats the tuff shit out there.  
<br />

<br />
Everyone says "well pristine rare armor owns".  Hello wtf.  You can get enough rares to be decked out in pristine (and your dog too) in 3 days in perma.  I mean do the epic zones 2-3 times and you are wiping your ass with rare crafted linen toilet paper.  How is that a challenge?  How does that show me and everyone else out there that my guildies work harder, look better, have better stats, than some guy that is exping to 50 still and farms named in Perma and group kills x2 weak mobs.
<br />

<br />
At this point, a money farmer perma-camping a named in EF/ Perma/ CT will have the same reward for botting 6 characters and selling pp on Ebay as do the hard working fellas of my guild that spend 6 hours raiding almost everynight.  
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: yellow"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">Hi - fix this.</span></span>
<br />

<br />
My suggestion - Never should a regular mob drop something that a raid mob would (x2 and better).  x2 - x3 - x4s  should have different loot tables - COMPLETELY different.  If you want to save time coding then sure... make like the all 50+ x2 mobs drop similar epic loot... x3 the same and x4 mob share similar tables.  Just not all one big ass pool of crap it randoms from on all epic raids.   Increasing the reward with the difficulty and epicness (x2 vs x4).  Rares should drop way less on regular named mobs.  <span style="font-weight: bold">Make some new uber loot looks and stats... </span>I dunno, put in a 50th lvl epic armor quest that is retarded hard that MAYBE 2-5 people will complete per class in a month or so.
<br />

<br />
Eventually the playerbase is going to shift to the right (IE higher lvl).  At this point will you be ready to keep the players by having content waiting for them?  4 chumpy 1 kill zones and a hand full of rare x4 mob spawns and 1 epic quest is not long term content... it is a band-aid.   <span style="font-weight: bold">Plan ahead for the wave of 50s coming, get worthwhile content </span>(not just an expansion ... tack on 25 lvls to get and some harder shit to exp on) <span style="font-weight: bold">that a person can do at 50</span>.  I have yet to hear about a 45+ SOLO zone.....  I understand catering to the masses to keep people interested, but god dam can we get some <span style="text-decoration: underline"><span style="font-weight: bold">proactivity</span></span> here and realize - EVERYONE IS GOING TO BE 50 EVENTUALLY.
<br />

<br />
Ya - so this went on for a bit more than I planned... call it therapy, call it anger, call it a llama...  I care about this game and the people I play with.  I believe in the game and it's developers.  Maybe Scott will read this - maybe not.   Trying to maintain a MMO for current profits and long term profits has to be a hard thing to do with all the competition out there.  The best businesses out there are 1 step ahead of their customers and competition.  They are developing the future and maintaining the present.  It is a tough job but I have faith the Devs and directors will come through.<br />_________________<br />Noah
<br />
50th Guardian
<br />
Officer of FoH</span><span
