          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody">Picture a man on a horse out in the wilderness several miles from the nearest outpost.  He rides along in a gentle breeze looking forward to cards, women and whiskey when suddenly he comes across another man, also on a horse...
<br />

<br />
The first man says to the second in a rather bewildered tone, "What in the hell are you doing?"    You see, the second man's horse is dead.
<br />

<br />
"I'm going to town, bubba!"
<br />
"But your horse.  It's dead!"  And with that, our hero moves off shaking his head sadly.
<br />

<br />
Well into the night, beating with his crop and pounding with his spurs sits our guy,  motionless and alone...the horse still dead.</span><span
class="gensmall"></span></td>
