        <tr>
          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody">The entire loot system needs to be looked at, imo. What was wrong with items having unique stat sets? Nothing. It allowed for much more customizability. With EQ2, you are stuck with Stamina and Agility on boots, Wisdom and Intelligence on helms, etc. (for the most part). The only thing that ever varies is quantity of stat.
<br />

<br />
I dunno about any of you, but the whole loot system seems to me a bit half-assed. At least in EQ1, they tried to make things seem unique and worth-while. In EQ2, I find a new piece of equipment I can and use, and it's like, "M'eh, what's next?"<br />_________________<br />Aegeras Ashenblade
<br />
<a href="http://www.tlwguild.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Last Word</a>
<br />
Innothule</span><span
