        <tr>
          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody">The pain of the Economy cannot be understated.  I just recently rerolled and started a bard-&gt;troubadour, and during 1-15 I made 5 gold.  4 gold from a Storm of Lightning, and 1 gold from 1500 vendor trash items.....small imbalance there. 
<br />

<br />
Though I'll add one more that really irks me...
<br />

<br />
I talked to quite a few of the EQ2 Devs in years past, and one thing they reiterated over and over to me was:  WE HATE BOTTOMFEEDING!
<br />

<br />
Seriously, there was no way around it, they swore up and down EQ2 was going to be vastly different than EQ1 in terms of forced camping.  Instead, we're right back where we started.  Instead of Epic Weapon quests, we have things like Lore&amp;Legend.  Trying to do your L&amp;L quests 40+ is pure futility.  For example, Faeries.  This is an L&amp;L you wont see until your 40-50.  Yet where is the best place to finish this quest?  A level 10 zone like Peat Bog, or Oakmyst Forest.  The same applies to lower level L&amp;Ls like Elementals, Golems, Skeletons.
<br />

<br />
It might not seem like that big of a deal to many, but it really chaps my ass after all the grandstanding I saw pre-release.  And there's nothing more that I hate than running over newbies just looking to get into the game.</span><span
class="gensmall"></span></td>
