        <tr>
          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody">I am very very impressed as a part time player with all the changes already added and on there way to the live servers. There is no doubt in my mind that this game was rushed to release but with saying that I will also say that they impress me on a daily basis with the effort and feedback they give back to the game and its community.
<br />

<br />
Loot tables are broken, not just for the Epic mobs.
<br />

<br />
It starts at level 10 and continues on to level 50. Some mobs are well balanced as far as what they give out and some are not.
<br />

<br />
If SOE has intended for mobs to share a general loot table (as it appears they have) then it seems that the tables are based off of level and not difficulty. This could only be for one reason in my mind, and that is that there is not enough loot in the game to support unique tables for all the encounters. That also says to me that they want you to get your rare loot from quests involving these rare kills if you want to have a special piece of gear.
<br />

<br />
I cannot say for certain since I am only level 30, but from all the posts I am seeing and all the similar gear I see for sale on the market, it is evident that the loot tables currently are very shallow.
<br />

<br />
I think that once they fix the messed up ecomnomy, take care of the rest of the class balancing issues and fix all the broken spells they may start to fix the loot tables  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
In 6 months there is no doubt in my mind that this game will be polished based on how much they are putting into the game on a daily basis. The question is can people wait that long?
<br />

<br />
I can...
<br />

<br />
Naz</span><span
class="gensmall"></span></td>
